INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (6,'Senior Product Manager - AI','See more open positions at Super Dispatch','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/super-dispatch-2#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/super-dispatch-2/jobs/56289215-senior-product-manager-ai','United States','data-science',1754956800,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/b9f59cc8-ab29-5c37-8e0b-570e7d544bea-1748914606','<div> <p>Super Dispatch is looking for a <strong>Senior Product Manager experienced in AI-powered product development</strong> to help design, build, and execute innovative initiatives for Super Dispatch platform product and broader AI platform capabilities. This role requires a lean product mindset and a proven track record of integrating AI and machine learning into successful B2B SaaS products. You’ll work alongside engineers, data scientists, and designers in a dynamic, fast-paced, and metrics-driven environment.</p> <p>Super Dispatch is a 100% distributed team, so this role can be done anywhere in the US (Must be authorized to work in the US).</p> <p><strong>About You</strong></p> <p>This is a fully remote role and an exciting opportunity for an experienced Product Manager who has <strong>shipped AI-driven products from ideation to scale</strong>. You’ll leverage your deep understanding of AI technologies—such as predictive analytics, natural language processing, and intelligent automation—to deliver high-value solutions for our customers.</p> <p>You’ll be based in the US but collaborate closely with our engineering and AI/ML teams in Central Asia, bridging time zones and translating complex technical capabilities into clear customer value.</p> <p><strong>Why Super Dispatch</strong></p> <p>At Super Dispatch, we’re not just digitizing the auto transport industry—we’re <strong>infusing it with intelligence</strong>. Our next-generation platform combines transportation management with AI-powered decision-making, automation, and data-driven insights to set a new standard for efficiency and customer experience.</p> <p>Our suite of tools—including Carrier TMS, Shipper TMS, SuperPay, and our groundbreaking Super Loadboard—are evolving to include <strong>AI-powered recommendations, workflow automation, and predictive analytics</strong>. These capabilities empower carriers, shippers, and brokers to make better decisions, reduce costs, and unlock new efficiencies at scale.</p> <p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p> <ul> <li>Collaborate with stakeholders to research, validate, and prioritize customer problems that AI and automation can solve</li> <li>Own the <strong>AI problem space</strong> for your product and customer segment, becoming an expert in how AI can enhance customer workflows, decision-making, and operational efficiency</li> <li>Define and execute the <strong>AI product vision and roadmap</strong> in alignment with the overall company strategy</li> <li>Define and monitor AI product KPIs such as prediction accuracy, model adoption, and ROI impact</li> <li>Partner with engineering, design, and data science teams to deliver innovative AI solutions that drive measurable outcomes</li> <li>Communicate progress, learnings, and risks regularly too stakeholders<br> </li> </ul> <p><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>5+ years of Product Management experience</strong>, with <strong>at least 2 years</strong> leading AI or ML-powered product initiatives for B2B SaaS solutions</li> <li>Degree in Computer Science, Data Science, or related field</li> <li>Successfully scaling AI-driven products from MVP to market adoption</li> <li>Experience turning AI/ML capabilities into customer-facing features with measurable business impact</li> <li>Experience in transportation/logistics or supply chain technology is nice to have</li> <li>Strong track record of working in metrics-driven, experimentation-focused environments<br>Comfortable working within cross-functional squads including engineers, data scientists, and product designers</li> <li>Experience owning business outcomes, product roadmap, and go-to-market strategies</li> <li>Proven ability to work with remote, distributed teams across multiple time zones</li> </ul> <p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>Great Culture</strong> - We strive for transparency and you’ll work with like minded highly motivated people excited about solving complex problems</li> <li> <strong>Great Insurance</strong> - We offer multiple health, dental &amp; vision plans with a portion of the employee premiums paid by the company</li> <li> <strong>Retirement</strong> - We provide both Stock Options and 401K with a company match</li> <li> <strong>Remote First Culture</strong> - We’re a 100% distributed team! </li> <li> <strong>Gym/Wellness Stipend</strong> - We provide a monthly stipend for gym memberships ($50/mo)</li> <li> <strong>Generous Time Off </strong>- Flex PTO policy so you can take the time you need, when you need it as well as 6-12 weeks paid paternity leave</li> <li> <strong>Great Gear</strong> - we’ll set you up for success with the latest tech and help you outfit your home office. And, a free Spotify premium account! </li> </ul>  <p><strong>Location Requirement:</strong><br> This position is only open to candidates located within the United States.</p> <p><strong>Citizenship Requirement:</strong><br> Due to the nature of the work and applicable federal regulations, candidates <strong>must be U.S. citizens</strong>. Proof of U.S. citizenship will be required during the hiring process.<br><br>If you’re passionate about building <strong>AI products that solve real-world problems</strong> and want to help shape the future of intelligent transportation, we’d love to talk.</p> <p>Super Dispatch takes a market-based approach to pay, which may vary depending on your location. The pay scale salary or On-Target Earnings (OTE, for Sales roles) range for this position represents the low, middle, and high end of the salary or OTE range for this position based on all US locations. To determine starting pay we carefully consider a variety of factors, including primary work location and an evaluation of a candidate’s skills, experience, market demands, and internal parity. Salary/OTE is just one component of our total rewards package. The pay scale or OTE ranges may be modified in the future.</p> <p>All regular full-time employees are also eligible for excellent Medical, Dental and Vision coverage with generous premium contributions for both employees and their families, the option of a Health Savings Account with Employer Match, Company paid disability and life insurance with opportunity to add additional coverage for you and your family.</p> <p>Super Dispatch provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws. As part of this policy and legal compliance, Super Dispatch will make reasonable accommodations for the known physical or mental limitations of an otherwise qualified individual with a disability who is an applicant or an employee unless undue hardship would result. Super Dispatch will also accommodate a religious belief or practice (including religious dress and grooming practices, such as religious clothing or hairstyles) if the accommodation is reasonable and will not impose an undue hardship.</p> <p>This policy applies to all terms and conditions of employment, including recruiting, hiring, placement, promotion, termination, layoff, recall, transfer, leaves of absence, compensation and training.</p> <p>Super Dispatch, Inc. will comply with any and all applicable local, city, county, state and federal laws, regulations and orders now in effect or which may hereafter be enacted.</p>  </div>');
