INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (8,'Senior Analytics Engineer','See more open positions at Healthie','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/healthie#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/healthie/jobs/56179571-senior-analytics-engineer','Remote','data-science',1754784000,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/c458b2e9-355d-5d7a-a524-701a5756dcce-1748914164','<p><strong>Healthie''s Mission</strong></p> <p>Healthie powers virtual-first care delivery, improving access to healthcare and enabling better healthcare outcomes through technology.</p> <p>We build infrastructure that all healthcare organizations need to perform virtual-first care. Our platform, which includes EHR, scheduling, and patient engagement solutions, empowers organizations of every size to build, customize, and scale their business.</p> <p>Today, we support thousands of organizations—from small private practices to multi-billion-dollar healthcare companies. With Healthie, our customers deliver care to millions of patients across the full spectrum of healthcare services, from preventative health and wellness to complex chronic care management.</p> <p>We believe the future of healthcare delivery is virtual-first, longitudinal, and collaborative. Learn more at: <a href="https://www.gethealthie.com">https://www.gethealthie.com</a>.</p> <hr> <p><strong>About the Role</strong></p> <p>We''re hiring a <strong>Senior Analytics Engineer </strong>to build and scale the data systems that transform how both our team and healthcare organizations understand their impact — from internal product metrics to customer-facing insights on patient engagement and care outcomes across our platform serving thousands of organizations.</p> <p>You''ll architect and develop robust analytics pipelines that turn complex healthcare data into actionable insights for both internal stakeholders and external customers. Working alongside engineering, product, and customer success teams, you''ll create intuitive self-service reporting tools, internal business dashboards, customer-facing analytics, and the foundational infrastructure powering Visualize, our analytics and reporting platform.</p> <p>This role puts you at the center of enabling data-driven decisions across Healthie and the healthcare organizations we serve. Your systems will help our internal teams optimize product development and business operations, while empowering external providers to track meaningful health outcomes, understand patient engagement, and streamline their care delivery — ultimately improving healthcare experiences for millions of patients nationwide.</p> <p><strong>Details, details</strong></p> <p>This is a full-time remote position</p> <p>Must be located in the U.S. and U.S. work authorization is required.</p> <p>The salary range is $180,000 - $200,000 per year + annual company bonus and benefits</p> <p><strong>About You</strong></p> <ul> <li>You have 5+ years of analytics engineering or data engineering experience, with strong skills in SQL and data pipeline development</li> <li>You''re proficient in working with large-scale databases (PostgreSQL preferred) and modern data stack tools, particularly dbt, Snowflake, and Metabase</li> <li>Knowledge of Python or Ruby for data processing, automation, and integrating with Healthie''s existing stack</li> <li>You''ve built production-grade analytics systems and self-service data platforms that serve external customers</li> <li>You''re skilled at transforming complex data into clean, actionable insights and customer-facing reportsYou think beyond one-off analyses — you build reusable, automated analytics infrastructure that scales with the business</li> <li>You prioritize data quality, privacy, and compliance, building systems that meet healthcare standards like HIPAA</li> <li>You implement robust data testing, monitoring, and observability practices to ensure reliable analytics systems</li> <li>Familiarity with data governance frameworks and metadata management</li> <li>You communicate clearly and collaborate effectively across technical and non-technical teams, including external customers</li> <li>Experience with healthcare analytics, BI tools, or building customer-facing data products is a plus </li> </ul> <p><strong>Interview Process</strong></p> <ul> <li>Video interview with Debbie, AI recruiter</li> <li>Initial Interviews:</li> <ul> <li>Quick chat with Katie, Director of Talent (20 minutes) </li> <li>Hiring Manager Interview with Ani, Director of Engineering (30 minutes)</li> </ul> <li>Complete our Take Home Assessment (asynchronous) </li> <li>Interview with Jae Lee, Staff Engineer and Stephen Ku (45 minutes)</li> <li>Final session with Cavan, CTO + cofounder (30 minutes)</li> <li>Reference Checks</li> </ul> <p>To learn more about Working at Healthie &amp; our benefits,<a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Yg-gwmd6LORDskg-mOFBMBhrRH9n_JILvUvNLv-gG2w/edit?tab=t.0"> click here</a>.</p> <p><em>Healthie participates in e-verify</em></p><div><p><em>Healthie is committed to equal employment opportunity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to and will not be discriminated against based on age, race, gender, color, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status, disability or any other protected category. We''re proud to be building a diverse and inclusive environment that encourages collaboration, creativity, and growth. Whatever your background, please apply if this is a role that would make you excited to come into work every day.<span> </span></em></p></div>');
