INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (25,'Senior Robotics Software Engineer','See more open positions at Crow Industries','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/crow-industries#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/crow-industries/jobs/56190938-senior-robotics-software-engineer','Scottsdale, AZ, USA','data-science',1754870400,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/d16b748c-58f2-5f12-9b79-06b2658b6e6a-1747445743','<div> <p><strong>ITAR Requirements</strong></p> <p>To conform to U.S. Government export regulations, the applicant must be a: (i) U.S. citizen or national, (ii) U.S. lawful permanent resident (aka green card holder), (iii) Refugee under 8 U.S.C. § 1157, or (iv) Asylee under 8 U.S.C. § 1158, or be eligible to obtain the required authorizations from the U.S. Department of State.</p>  <p><strong>About Us</strong></p> <p>Crow Industries (CI) is an innovative robotics startup building the most advanced autonomous ground vehicles in the world. We focus on the defense and mining industries with the intent to extend our operations to the Moon, Mars, and beyond. Our team is determined to push the boundaries of robotics and artificial intelligence to enable people to accomplish things that would otherwise be impossible. We thrive on figuring out the things no one has figured out yet.</p>  <p><strong>Job Description</strong></p> <p>We are seeking a highly motivated, skilled, and creative Robotics Software Engineer to join our team. In this role, you will play a pivotal part in developing and enhancing our Fenris and Vanir platforms. You will work on state-of-the-art robotics software, implement SLAM algorithms, and contribute to the development of our software stacks. Your innovative thinking, problem-solving abilities, and dedication to excellence will be instrumental in driving our technologies forward.</p>  <p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p> <ul> <li>Robotic Control: Design, develop, and deploy robotic control systems, including teleoperations, semi-autonomous, and fully autonomous solutions.</li> <li>Autonomous Operations: Develop and implement robust mapping, localization, and operational algorithms for structured and unstructured off-road environments.</li> <li>Swarm Coordination: Develop algorithms and systems to enable fleets of dozens to thousands of robots to coordinate as a team, with each robot operating independently towards a common goal under the supervision of a single human operator.</li> <li>Field Deployments: Support field teams to ensure high-quality performance of robotic assets during deployments, conducting high-pressure troubleshooting in real-time.</li> <li>Adaptive Problem Solving: Quickly adapt to changing project requirements and technical challenges with creative solutions.</li> <li>Documentation: Maintain comprehensive documentation of software design, implementation, and testing processes to ensure transparency and knowledge sharing.</li> <li>Demo Support: Collaborate with business development and engineering teams to support product demonstrations for potential clients and investors.</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Basic Qualifications</strong></p> <ul> <li>GSD!! (If you know, you know): Urgency, grit, tenacity, passion, integrity, high standards.</li> <li>Expertise in Python, CAN, C++, SLAM, ROS, and Gazebo.</li> <li>Real-world experience in field robotics, particularly off-road scenarios.</li> <li>Strong skills in Computer Vision, Perception, and sensor data integration.</li> <li>Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently.</li> <li>Exceptional communication skills and ability to work effectively in a team.</li> <li>Experience with version control systems (Git) and collaborative development.</li> <li>Strong documentation skills for technical transparency.</li> <li>Insane attention to detail and commitment to producing high-quality products.</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Preferred Skills and Experience</strong></p> <ul> <li>Familiarity with Machine Learning/Neural Networks for autonomous robots.</li> <li>Demonstrated ability to thrive in a fast-paced startup environment with frequently changing needs and requirements.</li> <li>Exposure to Cloud Computing (AWS) and containerization technologies (Docker/ContainerD)</li> <li>PhD or Master’s degree in Robotics, Computer Science, or a related field OR equivalent experience</li> <li>Military Veterans are encouraged to apply!</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Additional Requirements</strong></p> <ul> <li>Must be willing to work from our headquarters in Scottsdale, AZ.</li> <li>Must be willing to work extended hours and weekends as needed.</li> <li>Must be passionate and determined to do things that have never been done before.</li> <li>Occasional domestic and international travel may be required.</li> </ul>  <p>If you are a passionate, self-driven Robotics Software Engineer eager to contribute to an exhilarating future for humanity, we’d love to meet you!</p> </div>');
