INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (50,'Computer Aided Design Technician','See more open positions at OnStation','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/onstation#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/onstation/jobs/53820779-computer-aided-design-technician','Cleveland, OH, USA','design',1751760000,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/b47bbd45-67c5-5225-b56a-1da7a755f13d-1747703970','<div> <p><strong>CAD Technician</strong></p> <p><strong> </strong></p> <p>Job Type: Full Time</p> <p>Experience: 3-5 Years Minimum</p> <p>Location: Remote, Cleveland, OH </p> <p> </p>  <p>About The Position</p> <p>We are looking for a detail-oriented and dependable CAD Technician to support our engineering and geospatial workflows. This role is ideal for someone early in their career who is interested in civil design files and wants to gain hands-on experience working with digital project data.</p> <p>The CAD Technician will primarily be responsible for preparing, organizing, and running CAD files through our internal automation tools. This includes checking file structure, ensuring proper formatting, managing references, and assisting with the preparation of data for downstream use in GIS, field apps, or design systems.</p>  <p><strong>Here is your first mission, should you choose to accept it: On the first LinkedIn question screener, send us a DM and answer: What excites your about working with CAD files for roadway projects?</strong></p>   <p>Who We Are</p> <p>The Leading Digital Stationing Platform: With the OnStation app, CAD files for heavy highway road construction projects are viewable on any phone, allowing users to access a live digital station and offset reading wherever they are on the job. Everyone on site can capture what they see without wandering around or wasting time.</p>  <p>Our app supports a variety of heavy civil road construction organizations, such as asphalt paving companies, engineering/inspection and consulting firms, utilities, subcontractors, concrete pavers, as well as departments of transportation and cities and municipalities. We help them find their location out on the road construction project so they can collaborate and document their work more quickly and more safely.</p>  <p>Join us in creating a better future where reliable project data (pictures, chats, e-tickets, core tests, and much more) is captured on-site and is visible within the organization’s OnStation’s data portal. We’re helping the people who build our roads do their jobs more easily, and it all begins with the idea, “You are here.”</p> <p> </p>  <p>The Benefits</p> <p>At OnStation, we value committed and creative individuals by providing a rewarding work environment that emphasizes collaboration and innovation. We offer stimulating projects, competitive compensation packages—including vacation, PTO, and potential equity—and create a culture where together we strive to build something remarkable. Our foundation lies in developing exceptional solutions for our clients, driving business success and fostering growth in an inspiring workplace.</p> <ul> <li>Full-time salary with performance-based bonus potential</li> <li>Health, dental, and vision insurance</li> <li>401(k) with company match</li> <li>Generous PTO and flexible work schedule</li> <li>Opportunity to grow within a high-impact marketing team</li> </ul> <p><strong> </strong></p>  <p>Key Responsibilities</p> <ul> <li>Organize and process incoming DGN, DWG, and related CAD files</li> <li>Run files through automated workflows (e.g., batch processing, file conversions, metadata extraction)</li> <li>Check for missing reference files or inconsistencies in file structure</li> <li>Perform quality control checks on exported data and automation outputs</li> <li>"Clean up" Design files when necessary to provide the best user experience</li> <li>Help improve automation workflows through documentation and organization</li> <li>Store alignments graphically by tracing or recreating geometry from CAD or PDF plans provided. (This can be taught, but some knowledge would be preferred)</li> </ul> <p><strong> </strong></p>  <p>What will be required in this position</p> <ul> <li>Experience with CAD platforms such as MicroStation, OpenRoads, or AutoCAD (academic or professional)</li> <li>Familiarity with basic file types and structures used in civil design (e.g., DGN, DWG, KMZ, LandXML)</li> <li>Strong organizational skills and attention to detail</li> <li>Ability to follow established procedures and flag issues appropriately</li> <li>Comfort working with folders, file naming conventions, and project templates</li> <li>Self-motivated and time conscious with the ability to be part of a team via remote communication.</li> <li>Store<strong><em> (Horizontal Geometry) </em></strong>alignments graphically by tracing or recreating geometry from CAD or PDF''s</li> <li>Working in 2D drawings</li> </ul>   <p>Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) Statement</p> <p>At OnStation, we are committed to providing equal employment and advancement opportunities for all individuals, regardless of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, or any other characteristic protected by law. We believe that merit-based assessments evaluate individuals based on their abilities, potential, and accomplishments without bias. </p> <p>As we strive to revolutionize highway construction management through our innovative application and features, we invite individuals from diverse backgrounds to join us. Our goal is to shape the future of project management in the highway industry and beyond, including expansion into railroads, utilities, and commercial developments. Join us on this journey, showcase your skills, and be part of creating a significant impact in large-scale applications.</p> </div>');
