INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (70,'Mechatronics Engineer - Autonomous UAV Technology','See more open positions at Sees.ai','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/sees-ai#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/sees-ai/jobs/56102179-mechatronics-engineer-autonomous-uav-technology','chichester, uk','design',1754697600,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/69deb1aa-8c17-5800-afea-a75fa9631403-1747532199','<span id="spandesc"><p><span>Not every mechatronics role lets you take complete ownership of UAV systems from concept to flying missions. This one does.</span><br></p>  <p><span>Join a Boeing-backed team building autonomous drones that are already inspecting critical infrastructure for National Grid and other major operators.</span><br></p>  <div> <span> These aren''t prototypes gathering dust — they''re aircraft conducting real Beyond Visual Line of Sight missions across the UK today, and we need a mechatronics engineer who can own the entire development process.</span><br> </div>  <p><span><b>Why Join?</b></span><br></p>  <div> <span><b>Complete system ownership:</b><span> </span>Take responsibility for UAV systems from initial design through integration, production, and flight validation — you''ll own the entire process with focus on electronics and electrical systems.</span><br> </div>  <p><span><b>Real hands-on engineering:</b><span> </span>Electronic design, PCB layout, system integration, testing, production — all part of the job. This isn''t just design work.</span><br></p>  <p><span><b>Cutting-edge UAV technology:</b><span><b> </b></span>We''re the first UK company with routine BVLOS permissions in non-segregated airspace. You''ll be developing systems for technology that''s genuinely pioneering.</span><br></p>  <p><span><b>End-to-end responsibility:</b><span> </span>From initial concept through design, integration, production, and flight testing — you''ll see the complete journey and own every step.</span><br></p>  <p><span><b>Immediate impact:</b><span> </span>Your systems will be flying missions over power grids, inspecting critical infrastructure that keeps the lights on.</span><br></p>  <p><span><b>A company that''s scaling:</b><span> </span>With major clients already onboard and expanding operations across the UK and Europe, this is the right time to join.</span><br></p>  <p><span><b>The Role</b></span><br></p> <p><span>You''re a mechatronics engineer who doesn''t just want to work on one part of a system — you want to<span> </span><b>own the complete process from design to flight</b>.</span><br></p> <div> <span> You''re technical enough to design robust electronic systems, methodical enough to manage complex integration challenges, and driven enough to take responsibility for entire UAV systems with strong focus on the electronics and electrical aspects.</span><br> </div>  <p><span>This isn''t a role where you''re handed specifications to implement. You''ll take ownership of complete systems, making design decisions, managing integration challenges, overseeing production, and ensuring everything works flawlessly in flight.</span><br></p>  <p><span>Working as part of our Integration Team and reporting to the Integration Manager, you''ll be responsible for the electronic and electrical systems that enable our autonomous aircraft to operate safely and reliably in challenging real-world environments.</span><br></p>  <div> <span><b>What You''ll Do</b></span><br> </div> <ul><li> <span><b>System Design &amp; Ownership:</b><span> </span>Take complete responsibility for UAV systems from initial concept through to operational deployment — you own the entire process with primary focus on electronics and electrical systems.</span><br> </li></ul>  <ul><li> <span><b>Integration &amp; Development:</b><span> </span>Lead the integration of sensors, processors, communication systems, and power management into cohesive, flight-ready UAV systems.</span><br> </li></ul> <div> <span></span><br> </div> <ul><li> <span><b>Electronic and Electrical Design:</b><span> </span>Create electronic designs and PCB layouts and electrical routings that form the backbone of autonomous UAV operations, optimising for reliability and performance.</span><br> </li></ul> <div> <span></span><br> </div> <ul><li> <span>Production &amp; Build:<span> </span>Take hands-on responsibility for building and producing your systems, ensuring quality, consistency, and scalability as we grow.</span><br> </li></ul> <div> <span></span><br> </div> <ul><li> <span><b>Flight System Validation:</b><span> </span>Take ownership of testing and validating your systems through actual autonomous missions, with full responsibility for performance.</span><br> </li></ul> <div> <span></span><br> </div> <ul><li> <span>End-to-End Problem Solving:<span> </span>When issues arise anywhere in the system — design, integration, production, or flight — you''re the one who takes ownership and finds solutions.</span><br> </li></ul> <div> <span></span><b><br></b> </div> <ul><li> <span><b>Cross-functional Leadership:</b><span><b> </b></span>Work with software engineers and the operations teams, but you''re the one accountable for the overall system performance with focus on electronics and electrical aspects.</span><br> </li></ul> <div> <span></span><br> </div>  <div> <span><b>About You</b></span><br> </div> <ul> <li> <span><b>Hardware Development Experience:</b><span> </span>Strong background across design, integration, testing, and production of complex electronic systems</span><br> </li> <li> <span><b>Hands-on Skills:</b><span> </span>Comfortable with soldering, prototyping, debugging, and working with test equipment — this is practical engineering</span><br> </li> <li> <span><b>Technical Breadth:</b><span> </span>Experience with electronic design, PCB layout, system integration, or production processes</span><br> </li> <li> <span><b>Problem-Solving Mindset:</b><span> </span>Calm under pressure when systems don''t work first time, methodical in troubleshooting complex issues</span><br> </li> <li> <span><b>Fast-Paced Environment:</b><span> </span>Thrive in rapid development cycles where you see immediate results from your work</span><br> </li> <li> <span><b>Collaborative Approach:</b><span> </span>Work effectively with diverse teams — from software engineers to field operators</span><br> </li> <li> <span><b>Educational Background:</b><span> </span>Degree in Electronic, Electrical, or Mechanical Engineering, or equivalent practical experience</span><br> </li> </ul>  <div> <span><b>Bonus Points For:</b></span><br> </div> <ul> <li> <span>UAV, avionics, or aerospace hardware experience</span><br> </li> <li> <span>Production or manufacturing optimization experience</span><br> </li> <li> <span>Familiarity with safety-critical systems development</span><br> </li> </ul>   <div> <span><b>Why This Matters</b></span><br> </div>  <p><span>Your integrated systems will be flying autonomous missions over critical infrastructure, with you taking complete ownership from the initial electrical design through to operational performance. Unlike traditional engineering roles where you might work on one part of a system, here you''ll own the entire integration process for UAV electrical and electronic systems.</span><br></p>  <p><span>Join engineers from F1, aerospace, and AI backgrounds who are passionate about solving real-world problems with complete system ownership. This is your chance to take full responsibility for technology that genuinely matters.</span><br></p>  <p><b><span>Ready to own the complete integration process from design to flight?</span></b><br></p> </span>');
