</div></div> <div><div><div> <div><span>We combine:</span></div>  </div></div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>An international network of elite mentors and operators</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>A platform that turns growth into a process, not a guess</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>A proprietary methodology rooted in behavioral science and execution</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div>  </blockquote></div> <div><div><div>   </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div><span>WHY WE NEED YOUR HELP </span></div>  </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div>We are looking for a mid-level<span> Frontend &amp; UX Engineer</span> to craft responsive, accessible, and performant user interfaces. This role focuses on turning complex workflows into intuitive experiences, collaborating closely with design and product teams, and ensuring consistent implementation of design systems. It’s ideal for an engineer who combines technical frontend expertise with a strong user-centered mindset. </div>  </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div><span>OUR VALUES:</span></div>  </div></div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>People-Focused</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Relentless Growth</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Straightforward Execution</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Founder Mindset </div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div><div>   </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div><span>MAMBA MENTALITY:</span></div>  </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div>"Hard work outweighs talent.</div>  </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div>Mamba mentality is about 4 a.m. workouts, doing more than the next guy, and then trusting in the work you’ve put in when it’s time to perform. Without studying, preparation, and practice, you’re leaving the outcome to fate. I don’t do fate."</div>  </div></div></div> <div><div><div> <div>Kobe Bryant</div>  </div></div></div> <div><div> <h2> <span>🟠</span> About the <span>role</span> </h2>  </div></div>  <div><div> <h4><span>Primary Responsibilities</span></h4>  </div></div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div><span>User Research &amp; Insight Gathering</span></div>  </div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Conduct qualitative and quantitative <span>user research</span> (e.g., interviews, usability tests, surveys) to uncover user needs, pain points, and mental models.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Analyze behavioral data and feedback to inform design decisions.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Collaborate with product managers, developers, and stakeholders to align user needs with business goals.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div><span>UX &amp; Interaction Design</span></div>  </div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Design intuitive <span>user flows, wireframes, and interaction patterns</span> that make complex tasks simple and engaging.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Create <span>low- to high-fidelity prototypes</span> in tools like <span>Figma</span> to explore and communicate design solutions.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Define and document <span>interaction behaviors, micro-interactions, and UX patterns</span> for scalable implementation.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div><span>Usability, Accessibility &amp; Design Validation</span></div>  </div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Apply <span>usability heuristics, accessibility (a11y) standards, and inclusive design practices</span> to ensure products are usable by all.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Run <span>usability testing sessions</span> to validate design solutions, iterate quickly, and improve user experience.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Advocate for <span>evidence-based design</span> by leveraging insights, research findings, and data.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div> </div></div> <div><div> <h4><span>Secondary Responsibilities</span></h4>  </div></div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div><span>Collaboration &amp; Alignment</span></div>  </div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Work closely with Frontend Engineers to ensure design feasibility and fidelity in implementation.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div>Partner with Product Managers to shape <span>user stories,</span> acceptance criteria, feature definitions, requirements, and success metrics. </div>  </div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div><span>Design System &amp; Visual Consistency</span></div>  </div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Contribute to and evolve the <span>design system</span>, ensuring consistency, scalability, and reusability of components.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Champion <span>visual standards, UX guidelines, and documentation</span> to maintain product coherence.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div> </div></div> </div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Provide input in design critiques, ensuring solutions meet both user needs and technical constraints.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div> <div> <div><span>Mentorship &amp; Thought Leadership</span></div>  </div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Mentor junior designers, sharing knowledge and promoting best practices in UX, research, and prototyping.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div>Stay up-to-date with UX trends, tools, and emerging practices, bringing fresh ideas to the team.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div> </div></div>  <div><div role="note"> <div> <div><div><div><div><div><span aria-label="Callout icon" role="img">⚠️</span></div></div></div></div></div> <div><div><div><div> <div><span>We know you may not have all these characteristics but, if you think you are the right person, we would love to meet you.</span></div>  </div></div></div></div> </div>  </div></div> <div><div> <h4><span>Requirements</span></h4>  </div></div> <div><div> <div><div> <div><div><div> <div><span>Technical &amp; Design Skills:</span></div>  </div></div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>English level:</span> B2 or higher – we’re an international team; all meetings and communication are in English.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>Design Tools:</span> Expertise in <span>Figma</span> (or equivalent tools like Sketch, Adobe XD) for wireframing, prototyping, and design systems.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>Research Tools:</span> Familiarity with tools like <span>Maze, UserTesting, Dovetail</span>, or similar for conducting and analyzing user research.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>UX Principles:</span> Strong grasp of usability heuristics, interaction design principles, accessibility (WCAG 2.1+), and responsive design.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>Prototyping &amp; Testing:</span> Ability to create interactive prototypes and run usability tests to validate ideas.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>User Stories:</span> Experience writing or contributing to <span>user stories and acceptance criteria</span>.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>Metrics &amp; Analytics (Nice to Have):</span> Basic understanding of product analytics tools (e.g., Mixpanel, GA4) to inform design with data.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> <div><div>  <div><div> <div> <span>AI Integration (Nice to Have):</span> Experience designing for AI-centered user experiences, e.g., chatbots, recommendation systems, or LLM-powered interfaces.</div>  </div></div> </div></div> </div></div>  <div><div> <div><div><div> <div><span>Soft Skills:</span></div>  </div></div></div> <div><div>  <div><div