INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (78,'Full Stack Engineer','See more open positions at Reportwell','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/reportwell#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/reportwell/jobs/56004471-full-stack-engineer','Detroit, MI, USA','design',1754524800,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/f2894b0e-4975-58d8-8bf1-8275e7de2f54-1748568471','<div> <p><strong>Company Overview:</strong></p> <p>Reportwell is a pioneering platform dedicated to simplifying regulatory compliance and reporting for schools, authorizers, districts, and state agencies. Founded in 2023, Reportwell is designed to streamline the often complex and time-consuming tasks associated with compliance, ensuring that educational institutions consistently meet their regulatory obligations.</p>  <p><strong>Position Overview</strong></p> <p>Reportwell is seeking a Full Stack Engineer to drive the development of our SaaS platform, supporting public sector clients with powerful, user-friendly reporting tools. In this role, you’ll build and maintain end-to-end application features, from intuitive front-end components to secure, scalable backend services—while also contributing to infrastructure and DevOps best practices.</p> <p>This position is ideal for a product-oriented engineer with strong backend experience, solid frontend proficiency, and hands-on AWS knowledge. You’ll work closely with a cross-functional team and report to the Chief Product Officer. </p> <p>This is a hybrid role - this Full Stack Engineer will be working in-person at our Detroit office 3 days a week and 2 days remotely. </p>  <p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>Full Stack Development: </strong>Design, build, and maintain web application features using modern full stack technologies. </li> <li> <strong>Backend Engineering: </strong>Architect and build secure, scalable APIs and background services, ensuring performance and maintainability (Python, Django, Typescript, PostgreSQL, Redis, DynamoDB).</li> <li> <strong>Frontend Engineering: </strong>Implement responsive UI components and seamless user experiences using a component-based frontend framework (React/Redux).</li> <li> <strong>Cloud Infrastructure:</strong> Improve our AWS environment (including EC2, Fargate, IAM, S3, RDS). Troubleshoot and optimize cloud configurations and service interactions.</li> <li> <strong>DevOps Support:</strong> Contribute to CI/CD pipelines, containerization (Docker), orchestration (ECS or similar), and monitoring systems. Participate in on-call rotation and system troubleshooting.</li> <li> <strong>Technical Strategy:</strong> Work with leadership on architectural decisions, technical roadmap planning, and long-term platform evolution.</li> <li> <strong>Team Collaboration:</strong> Conduct code reviews, and participate in sprint planning. Collaborate with design and product to align engineering with business goals.</li> <li> <strong>AI Integration:</strong> Integrate AI and automation tools to streamline reporting workflows for clients.</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>Experience:</strong> 3+ years in full-stack development with emphasis on backend services, cloud infrastructure, and system design.</li> <li> <strong>System Design:</strong> Understanding of containers, RESTful APIs, relational databases (PostgreSQL preferred), and scalable application architecture.</li> <li> <strong>AWS Proficiency:</strong> Experience with AWS (IAM, EC2/Fargate, RDS, S3, CloudWatch, and troubleshooting across services).</li> <li> <strong>DevOps Skills:</strong> Experience with CI/CD tools (e.g., GitHub Actions), infrastructure-as-code (e.g., Terraform), and Docker.</li> <li> <strong>Technical Stack:</strong> Proficient in Python, Django, Typescript, React/Redux, PostgreSQL, Redis, DynamoDB, and cloud-native application design patterns.</li> <li> <strong>Communication:</strong> Strong technical communication skills with the ability to collaborate across teams and explain complex systems to non-technical stakeholders.</li> <li> <strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience preferred.</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Compensation &amp; Benefits</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>Base Salary:</strong> $90,000 - $115,000 per year</li> <li> <strong>Performance Bonus:</strong> Up to 10% of annual salary</li> <li> <strong>Healthcare:</strong> Medical, dental, and vision reimbursement</li> <li> <strong>401(k):</strong> 6% match, fully vested after 2 years</li> <li> <strong>Equity vesting: </strong>Available for select candidates</li> <li> <strong>PTO:</strong> 24 days annually + national holidays</li> <li> <strong>Flexibility: </strong>in-person in our Detroit office 3 days a week. 2 days remote.</li> </ul> </div>');
