INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`,`position_name`,`organization_title`,`organization_url`,`job_url`,`location`,`labor_function`,`posted_date`,`logo_url`,`description`) VALUES (99,'Staff Product Designer (100% remote role in EMEA)','See more open positions at Testlio','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/testlio#content','https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/testlio/jobs/54193377-staff-product-designer-100-remote-role-in-emea','Remote','design',1752192000,'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/17d9185b-1399-5bb7-b219-cf74aa4f6902-1748914598','<div> <div> <p>Location: This is a 100% remote role open to those who reside in the EMEA region. Due to our compensation strategy, we are not considering applicants from high-cost-of-living locations such as Benelux, DACH, France, Nordics, or the UK.</p> <h2>About the job </h2> <p>Testlio’s fully managed crowdsourced testing platform integrates expert, on-demand testers directly into your release process. Ship faster and more confidently with global coverage across 600,000+ devices, 800+ payment methods, 150+ countries, and 100+ languages. To learn more, visit <a href="https://testlio.com/">www.testlio.com</a>.</p> <p>We’re looking for a <strong>Staff Product Designer</strong> to own end-to-end design across our product and help define how design works at Testlio. Learn more about our Product team <a href="https://testlio.com/work/product/">here</a>. </p> <h3>Why you will love this job?</h3> <ul> <li> <strong>You’ll shape the product, not just design it</strong>. With no product managers, design leads the work. You’ll drive direction, own decisions, and collaborate directly with engineers who care about quality.</li> <li> <strong>You’ll work on everything</strong>. From redesigning legacy tools to launching new features and improving design systems. Your work will shape how the platform feels end to end.</li> <li> <strong>You’ll help define the design culture</strong>. You’re joining early and will set the standard for how we work.</li> </ul> <h3>Why you will love being a part of Testlio?</h3> <ul> <li> <strong>Great Culture:</strong> Testlio is a female-founded company, and half our team identifies as women. We’re proud of our <a href="https://testlio.com/culture/">inclusive, purpose-driven culture </a>where people genuinely enjoy collaborating. As part of our team (we call ourselves TestLions), you’ll help create exceptional digital experiences for our customers, while also contributing to our freelance network and social impact initiatives like <a href="https://testlio.com/ignite/">Ignite.</a> </li> <li> <strong>Remote Work: </strong>Our culture is built around remote work. We’ve created systems to allow us to successfully work together asynchronously as a <a href="https://testlio.com/blog/building-a-strong-culture-remotely/">fully remote and globally distributed team. </a>Testlio provides the tools and guidance for everyone to succeed in their careers in a fully remote setting. Our working style encourages everyone to make decisions, communicate effectively, and work at a sustainable pace. </li> <li> <strong>Investment in You: </strong>Your growth and well-being matter to us. You’ll have flexible paid time off—including national holidays, personal days, and sick days—plus stock options so you can grow with Testlio. We also provide a $300 annual learning stipend to support your personal and professional development.</li> <li> <strong>Winning Business:</strong> Testlio is growing, profitable, and cash-strong. We are leading our industry with <a href="https://testlio.com/customers/">exceptional clients</a> who provide us with a high NPS score and a 4.7 rating on G2. Our business model is global, enterprise, and subscription-based. Several of our largest clients have been with us for 7+ years, and many spend $500K+/year with Testlio. </li> </ul> <h3>What would your day look like?</h3> <ul> <li>Leading cross-functional discussions to define product functionality and user flows.</li> <li>Making strategic product decisions alongside engineering.</li> <li>Crafting high-fidelity, production-ready designs that meet both user and business needs, with strong attention to detail, visual polish, and usability.</li> <li>Prototyping and iterating on new features to explore ideas and validate interactions</li> <li>Creating clear, useful documentation to support implementation and ensure alignment, helping to foster a culture of constructive critique and iteration.</li> <li>Collaborating with engineers to refine edge cases, ensure feasibility, and uphold design quality.</li> <li>You’ll evolve our design system to support scalability and consistency across the platform.</li> </ul> <h3>What do you need to succeed?</h3> <p><strong>Technical Skills</strong></p> <ul> <li> <strong>Extensive Design Experience</strong>: 7+ years in product design, with a portfolio showing end-to-end ownership of complex products, especially in B2B SaaS.</li> <li> <strong>Design Systems Expertise</strong>: Proven expertise in building and scaling design systems, evolving them without creating overhead.</li> <li> <strong>Cross-Functional Collaboration</strong>: Strong collaboration with engineering teams, with the ability to communicate design intent clearly and effectively.</li> <li> <strong>User-Centered Design</strong>: Confident application of UX principles to deliver user-focused solutions, balancing experience, intuition, and established patterns over formal research when appropriate.</li> </ul> <p><strong>Human Skills</strong></p> <ul> <li>Strategic mindset to connect design decisions with product and business outcomes.</li> <li>Comfort working in ambiguous situations, proactively driving projects forward without complete information.</li> <li>Clear and concise written and verbal communication skills, with openness to feedback and critical questions.</li> <li>Leadership through context and example, setting high standards through individual contributions and collaboration.</li> <li>Curiosity and commitment to continuous learning, staying up to date with tools and trends in design systems, front-end development, and AI.</li> </ul> <h3>What is the application process?</h3> <p>We do our best to bring on individuals who will be excited about their role and have the potential for a great future with Testlio. Since we are 100% distributed, we’d like you to meet with multiple people from our organization to give you an idea of who you would be working with, your role expectations, etc. Our interview process can take about 3 to 4 weeks to complete. </p> <ul> <li>Application</li> <li>Recruiter interview</li> <li>TestGorilla assessment</li> <li>~ 3# Team and Stakeholder interviews</li> <li>Reference checks</li> <li>Offer</li> </ul> <h3>Diversity and Inclusion</h3> <p>Testlio is an equal-opportunity employer deeply committed to creating an inclusive environment for people of all backgrounds and identities. We are female-founded, and 46% of our team members identify as women. For more information, see the <a href="https://testlio.com/diversity-equity-and-inclusion/">DEI section</a> of our website.</p> <div><a href="#">Apply now</a></div> </div> </div>');
